# ============================================================
# Frontend Environment Configuration Example
# ============================================================
# Copy this file to .env and update the values for your setup

# API Base URL - where your backend REST API is running
REACT_APP_API_BASE=http://localhost:5000/api

# Socket.io URL - for real-time WebSocket connections
REACT_APP_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:5000

# ============================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# ============================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env (without the .example extension)
# 2. Update the URLs to match your backend server
# 3. Variables must start with REACT_APP_ to be accessible in React
# 4. Changes to .env require restarting the dev server
# 5. Never commit .env file to version control (use .gitignore)

# ============================================================
# Environment-Specific Examples:
# ============================================================

# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# REACT_APP_API_BASE=http://localhost:5000/api
# REACT_APP_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:5000

# PRODUCTION (Deployed):
# REACT_APP_API_BASE=https://your-backend-domain.com/api
# REACT_APP_SOCKET_URL=https://your-backend-domain.com

# STAGING:
# REACT_APP_API_BASE=https://staging-api.your-domain.com/api
# REACT_APP_SOCKET_URL=https://staging-api.your-domain.com

# ============================================================
# How to Use:
# ============================================================
# 1. cd smart-queue-frontend
# 2. cp .env.example .env
# 3. Edit .env with your actual backend URLs
# 4. npm start
